added.title: Wonderful World
added.description: Nia shows Thomas and Diesel how much unique beauty exists in Sodor, which comes in handy when they need plants to beautify a Plaza in Vicarstown.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Whistle Woes
added.description: When Thomas's whistle suddenly stops working, he learns that he doesn't need his whistle to still be himself.
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Caillou Makes a Meal/Caillou's New Groove/Caillou Goes Bowling
added.description: Caillou makes pizza for dinner with his family./Mommy and Daddy are gone overnight and Grandpa and Grandma are babysitting./Caillou is hesitant to try bowling.

added.title: Big Kid Caillou/Caillou's Glasses/Caillou's Dance Party
added.description: Caillou's older friend Andre is coming over to play./When Mommy gets a new pair of specs, Caillou wants glasses too./Miss Martin is throwing a dance party.

added.title: Caillou's Shadow/High Flyers/Caillou's Leaf Pile
added.description: Caillou likes it when Miss Martin calls him a shadow scientist./Daniel comes for a visit./Caillou has fun jumping in the fall leaves with Daddy.

added.title: Sharing the Rocketship/Coach Granpa/The Safety Helper
added.description: Caillou and Leo decide to go 'halvsies' on a toy shuttle./Grandpa is coaching Caillou's soccer team./Caillou is very proud when Miss Martin makes him "Safety Helper".

added.title: Rushing the Raspberry/Wait to Skate/Caillou's Hiccups
added.description: Caillou is helping Mommy take care of a raspberry bush./Daddy is building an ice rink in the backyard./A spaghetti dinner (and a lot of giggling) result in Caillou getting the hiccups.

added.title: Skateboard
added.description: Bing and Flop are in the park when Pando vooshes past on his skatebaord. Pando agrees to let Bing try out his skateboard. But what happens when Bing comes to a steep hill and the skateboard goes faster and faster?

added.title: Butterfly
added.description: Bing and his friends are playing at Amma's today when a beautiful butterfly comes inside. But what happens when Bing catches the butterfly in his hands while trying to save it?

added.title: Chalk Dinosaur
added.description: Bing wants to draw a big picture so Flop finds him some chalk to draw on the sidewalk outside their house. But what happens when a big rain cloud comes just as Bing's finished his chalk dinosaur?

added.title: Potato
added.description: Bing and Sula find a potato with a nose on it in Amma's garden, and they want to keep it. So they call it Nosey. But, what will happen when they show Nosey how to go down the slide?

added.title: Rainy Boots
added.description: It's a wet, drippy day and Bing has his rainy boots on to help Flop take the trash out. While splish splashing outside, what will happen when Bing does a BIG SPLASH and finds his rainy boots have holes in them?

added.title: Scary Noises
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato are out for an adventure in the Vamoosh but have to land on a strange planet when a part of the Vamoosh falls off. Whilst searching for the missing part, Pato gets scared because he hears a strange, scary noise. They both realize there is nothing to be scared of and the alien just wants to make friends.

added.title: Not in My Backyard
added.description: Pocoyo discovers some old rubbish and decides to have a clear out. Baby Bird, Pato and Elly do the same. Soon there's a huge pile of rubbish, and it turns out it's on Caterpillar's doorstep. The rubbish keeps getting thrown around until finally Pocoyo follows the rubbish and realizes it's just going in a circle. In order to break the cycle, Pocoyo helps his friends make some new fun toys and games out of the rubbish.

added.title: Vamoosh on the Loosh
added.description: Pocoyo promises to teach Baby Bird to drive the Vamoosh but keeps putting it off. Fed up, Baby Bird decides to have a go on his own but he doesn't know how. The Vamoosh spins out of control. Pocoyo realises he must keep to his promise and teach Baby Bird to drive properly.

added.title: Detective Pocoyo
added.description: Elly is aghast to realize that her darling doll is missing. Detective Pocoyo decides to help Elly and he looks for clues as to where her doll might be. While Pocoyo goes back to the scene of the crime, Elly finds that she had her doll all along: it wasn't lost at all, she'd simply mislaid it. Elly is too embarrassed to own up and tells Pocoyo she doesn't need her doll anymore. But Detective Pocoyo uncovers the truth and the mystery is solved.

added.title: Scooter Madness
added.description: Pocoyo and Pato find Elly's scooter and decide to take it back to her. Pato enjoys showing off his scooter skills and quickly forgets who it belongs to. Pato's scooter tricks get bigger and bigger until eventually he breaks the scooter into pieces. Pocoyo and Pato try to fix the scooter but it's no good. However will they tell Elly? At first they try to cover up what they've done but eventually they have to confess. Thankfully Elly is not upset with them as she has another scooter and is just pleased her friends told the truth in the end.

added.title: That Ol' Time Rock Rolls!/Make Like a Banana and Split
added.description: When Big Old Boulder rolls down the hill towards the museum, Berta needs the Mechas help to keep it stable./It's Food Day in Pretty Big City, but the Mechas need to help when the banana atop the banana split statue is not split!

added.title: Magnet Mayhem/Stop That Train
added.description: The magnet crane at the construction site accidentally turns on, sucking up all the metal, including the Mecha Builders!/Roof is delivering eggs to Marwyn at the Train Station, that is, until the train pulls into the station and can't stop!

added.title: Bye Bye Bee/Jeepers Peepers/House is Breathing
added.description: Saying goodbye can be hard, but there are ways to feel close to your friends./ Can Dimples finally beat Weebscuit at a staring competition?/ Lucas is convinced House is alive when the heating vent comes on.

added.title: Boingo/Findley's Bad Day/You Rang
added.description: Lucas, Findley and Bodhi become obsessed with a new toy called Boingo./ Findley is convinced House is out to get him./ Arlo is missing his mother, so Lucas gives him a bell to ring if he needs Lucas's help - bad idea.

added.title: Morel in the Dark
added.description: When Mush-Mush discovers that Morel is afraid of the dark, he suggests that Chep, Lilit and he take the Mushlets to their first overnight forest camp. Morel is relieved. But when Mush-Mush and his friends later come back, panicked, and reveal that the Mushlets have disappeared, Morel has no choice but to face his fear and join our friends on their rescue mission in the dark!

added.title: Rise and Funshine
added.description: Funshine learns he can be as fearless as one of his super hero comic book characters when the Team falls into a magical sleep. To awaken them, he must transport them in the Cloudseeker to a special place in the Silver Lining - but he has never driven it before, and must learn from a comical "How To Pilot the Cloudseeker" video hosted by Grumpy.

added.title: Road Trip
added.description: On a mission to a remote area of the Silver Lining, Cheer questions the directions from Bedtime's maps. Everyone else backs Bedtime: he's never been wrong before! When the directions turn out to be wrong and lead them into danger, Cheer must trust her instincts to find a way out of the mess.

added.title: Bouncing Back
added.description: Mush-Mush is very proud he invented a new game called Fruity Bounce, where he and his friends bounce as high as possible on the bouncier fruits they can find. Little did he know, the Mushups were fruit-bouncing way before he, Chep and Lilit did. So, Mush-Mush decides that if he can't be the inventor of the game, he'll at least be the best at it. Mushlers vs Mushups, game on!

added.title: Pouting Match
added.description: Lola tries pouting to get what she wants, and soon all the babies are doing it.

added.title: Let Them Make Cake
added.description: Melissa wants cake, but she wants the other babies to bake it for her.

added.title: Petunia the Piggy Bank
added.description: The kids start getting an allowance but only Petunia thinks to save for something special.

added.title: A Pastime for Petunia
added.description: Petunia has a difficult time finding a hobby that doesn't imitate the other babies' interests.

added.title: Mind Your Manners
added.description: The babies learn proper dinner etiquette when preparing to dine out with Granny.

added.title: They Sent Us a Pie/Dust in the Wind
added.description: A giant pie is sent to Pretty Big City to stop an asteroid… but the Mechas and friends have eaten the whole thing!/The Singing Stone Heads are ready to perform at the Museum, but when they open their mouths, they sneeze instead of sing!

added.title: Sliding/Spinning Webs
added.description: Lucas and Findley find an ice cube. When Lucas rides the ice cube in the sink and falls down the drain, a scared Findley rallies to save him./ Lucas questions his spider-hood when he can't spin a web properly.

added.title: The Art of Friendship
added.description: When Chanterelle sees how good Lilit is at painting, she offers to help her dig into her talent. But Lilit's art lessons conflict with the fun project she has been working on with Mush-Mush and Chep. And when she sees that her friends are having a great time without her, Lilit is seriously annoyed which her paintings start showing.

added.title: The Rollinator
added.description: Chep is so good at moss-marbles, no one wants to play him anymore! No one except Sumush who reveals himself to be a tough competitor. To Chep's disbelief, Sumush keeps on winning. But Lilit and Mush-Mush convince their friend not to give up. Chep decides to play his favourite moss-marble: the Rollinator. The one marble he never risked playing before.

removed.title: Music
removed.description: Bing, Sula and Pando are making music with Flop and Amma. Everyone has their own instruments, but they all want the drum. Pando gets to go first, but what will happen when it's time to swap and Sula gets the drum next?

removed.title: Water, Water Everywhere
removed.description: Grumpy doesn't believe Funshine's warning that an invisible "Big Blob in the sky" is stealing water from a Whiffle garden -- he has pulled too many practical jokes before. To save the garden and his own credibility, Funshine must discover the truth of the menacing "Big Blob."

removed.title: Elly's Shoes
removed.description: Elly gets a fancy new pair of dressing up shoes. She loves wearing them so much that she won't take them off, even to go to bed!

removed.title: Cereal Boxing
removed.description: The kids become obsessed with getting the prizes from boxes of sugary cereal.

removed.title: Who Said That?
removed.description: Daffy learns a bad word and must learn not to use it.

removed.title: Caillou's Cricket/Dog Dilemma/The Spider Issue
removed.description: Caillou inadvertently brings a cricket in the house./When Sarah gets a new dog, Caillou is actually a little jealous./Caillou feels afraid of real spiders.

removed.title: Looking After Flop
removed.description: Flop is sick and Bing explains that he wants to take care of him. So Bing tells Flop to sit on the sofa and gives him a pillow and a blanket, and Hoppity Voosh too! But making honey lemon is tricky hard.

removed.title: What's Ringette?/Rainy Day at the Beach/Caillou Climbs
removed.description: Caillou and Leo want to play hockey./Caillou and his family are supposed to be enjoying a nice day./Mommy takes Caillou and Clementine to an indoor rock climbing wall.

removed.title: Big Scary Slide
removed.description: There's lots of new exciting playground rides in Pocoyoland including one huge daring slide. Pocoyo is too scared to give it a go. Pocoyo bravely helps his friend and overcomes his fear.

removed.title: The Magic of Spring
removed.description: Bugs' failure as a magician turns to success when he experiences the true magic of nature.

removed.title: Caillou Roller Skates/Say Lettuce!/Caillou Tries to Whistle
removed.description: Caillou wants to learn how to roller skate./Caillou wants to take a picture of a bunny rabbit in Grandma's garden./ Clementine can whistle, and Caillou can't!

removed.title: Caillou the Patient/Caillou the Police Officer/Grandpa's Friend
removed.description: While pretending to be a jet pilot Caillou falls down and scrapes his knees./When the traffic lights near school stop working a policeman comes to direct traffic./Grandpa takes Caillou to the park one fine day to meet his friend George.

removed.title: The Ultimate Bad Seed
removed.description: Malcom becomes the new boss of Blusterland when he tricks Bluster into letting him transfer his inner-badness into a Bad Seed, leaving Bluster a polite shell of his former self. To neutralize the dangerous Seed before Malcom can use it to turn the Silver Lining into a giant Blusterland, the Care Bears must transfer its bad energy back into the only thing that can hold it, Bluster himself!

removed.title: For Whom the Toll Calls
removed.description: Petunia and Tweety learn how to call long distance and amass a huge phone bill.

removed.title: Pull Together/Lift Up and Lift Off
removed.description: Ranger Nat is stuck at the bottom of the crevice, but the problem grows when Mecha Abby also gets stuck./Zee is ready to launch his rocket into space, but when the launchpad breaks, the rocket is launched into the farm instead.

removed.title: I'm Taking You In/Something Up There/Home Sweet Home
removed.description: When Arlo's mom is out, Lucas looks after him. How hard can it be?/ After hearing a screech from the fireplace, Lucas journeys up to find what is causing the noise./ Lucas and friends find a Gingerbread House and can't resist eating it.

removed.title: Dragon Breath
removed.description: Bing and Pando are blowing steamy dragon breath outside when they find an icicle that makes Bing's hands icy cold! So they go inside for some hot chocolate. What happens when Bing doesn't wait for the hot chocolate to cool down?

removed.title: Pocoyo's Balloon
removed.description: Pocoyo is taking a walk with his beloved balloon when he is momentarily distracted by Loula and accidentally lets go of the balloon. He is flabbergasted as it drifts away up into the sky, and irreconcilably down in the dumps. Until we help him to realize that some things are more lasting than balloons: friends!

removed.title: Who's' calling Me Now?
removed.description: Pocoyo finds a box of unusual whistles. To his delight he discovers that each whistle makes a different noise and summons a different one of his chums. Fun until the tables are turned on Pocoyo and there's a whistle that summons him too. Everyone realizes how silly they're being.

removed.title: Hippoty Hoppity Voosh
removed.description: Voooooosh! Bing and Sula are vooshing Hoppity and Fairy Hippo up higher and higher. What will happen when Fairy Hippo flies up a little too high and doesn't come back down again?

removed.title: A Light Delivery
removed.description: When Thomas accidentally breaks a light he's hauling to the Sodor Festival of Lights, he learns the best way to be the #1 engine is to be honest when you make a mistake.
removed.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

removed.title: New Cat in Town
removed.description: Sylvester is jealous of the attention baby Pepe is receiving.

removed.title: Come On Charlie
removed.description: Charlie is coming! And Bing has planned lots of games to play with him. But what happens when Charlie doesn't want to play any of the games Bing has put out?

removed.title: Duck Stuck
removed.description: Pocoyo finds a strange door. When he opens it, it seems to lead to the sky. Every time Pocoyo opens the door it seems to open up somewhere new.

removed.title: A Sweet and Sour Day/Caillou's Puppet Show/Caillou's Collection
removed.description: Caillou is helping Grandma water her flowers and fill the birdbath./Caillou and his friends Jason and Jeffrey make finger puppets at playschool and decide to put on a puppet show./In the park Caillou starts a new hobby - collecting rocks!

removed.title: The Paint Problem
removed.description: Thomas needs repainting and must be patient as he dries, even though he feels like he's missing out.
